caption: Clean place, instructors made it easy & the food was great

Love love Koki’s Kitchen. Samosas are delicious w the two different chutneys, these are pre-ordered. And the Korma curry paste, it smell as wonderful as it tastes!  Curry in a hurry and easy to make.  Just added coconut milk & a some water then added frozen vegetables. Curry sauce is served. Eating with or without rice. I also added her masala peanuts on top of curry and I just love the crunchiness to the curry!  Don’t hesitate and ask place  your order.  Koki also does Indian cooking lessons. It’s fun & very informative ❤️

If you want tasty, wholesome and soul satisfying Indian food, Koki’s kitchen is the best.  I have known Koki for a few years now and she is truly passionate about cooking. Her food exemplifies that to a tee. So far we have tried rajma, Chole, tadka dal, dal makhani, paneer tikka masala and all were delicious! I know we will continue to order from her.

We had a delicious, fresh meal from Koki’s Kitchen!  Koki takes care to understand what her customers want, communicated when needed for changes, and provided flexibility for pick up. I think the best compliment I can give is that Koki’s food reminds me of my mother’s— and that’s saying a lot!
